Definition.WordDefinition:
Inhale \In*hale"\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Inhaled}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Inhaling}.] [L. inhalare to breathe upon; pref. in- in + halare to breathe: cf. F. inhaler. Cf. {Exhale}.] To breathe or draw into the lungs; to inspire; as, to inhale air; -- opposed to exhale. [1913 Webster]
Martin was walking forth to inhale the fresh breeze of the evening. --Arbuthnot. [1913 Webster]

Definition.WordDefinition: inhaled \inhaled\ adj. drawn into the lungs; breathed in; as, inhaled smoke can damage the lungs. Inverse of exhaled. [WordNet 1.5]
inhaled adj : drawn into the lungs; breathed in; "inhaled smoke can damage the lungs" [ant: {exhaled}]
